org.cpsolver.ifs.assignment.context

Class AssignmentContextReference<V extends Variable<V,T>,T extends Value<V,T>,C extends AssignmentContext>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cpsolver.ifs.assignment.context.AssignmentContextReference<V,T,C>
  • Type Parameters:
    V - Variable
    T - Value
    C - Assignment Context

    public class AssignmentContextReference<V extends Variable<V,T>,T extends Value<V,T>,C extends AssignmentContext>
extends Object
    A reference to an assignment context. A reference is created by a class requiring an assignment context HasAssignmentContext by calling Model.createReference(HasAssignmentContext). This reference can be stored with the class implementing the HasAssignmentContext interface in place of the assignment context AssignmentContext. Assignment context can be than retrieved from an assignment by calling Assignment.getAssignmentContext(AssignmentContextReference). This method also create a new context if there is none associated with the assignment yet for the given reference.

    Method getIndex() can be used to index stored contexts. A new assignment context can be created for a reference by calling HasAssignmentContext.createAssignmentContext(Assignment) on the getParent().
